div.div: Goal: Create a form on homepage that passes results to a landing page with a google map that filters the map based on the form input

You should use POST method in your form if it contains sensitive information (like passwords...), or you can use GET method in your form if you don't mind if other users can see it... Example:
//You can use POST instead of GET Name:
E-mail:
If the user clicks the submit button, the form data will be sent to the landing page's PHP file (whose address is in the "action" parameter) via GET (or POST) for processing. > What is the difference between POST and GET? https://www.w3schools.com/tags/ref_httpmethods.asp > How to redirect to another page using PHP's header function? https://www.w3schools.com/php/func_http_header.asp --- Then, the landing page's php file should retrieve the submitted data via '$_POST["input field's name"]' or '$_GET["input field's name"]' --- Example for print the values: Welcome
